ery popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Lacy was born about 1160, in Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales. She married Robert de Mohaut. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1160–":"umbes 1160–Surnud","1165–1210":"1165–1210","1178–1231":"1178–1231","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1245":"1245","1178":"1178","1210":"1210","1231":"1231","1165":"1165","1160":"1160","1182":"1182","Abt 1180":"umbes 1180","1180":"1180","Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Hawarden, Flint, Wales":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1160–":"noin 1160–Kuollut","1165–1210":"1165–1210","1178–1231":"1178–1231","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","about 1160":"noin 1160","1245":"1245","1178":"1178","1210":"1210","1231":"1231","1165":"1165","1160":"1160","1182":"1182","Abt 1180":"noin 1180","1180":"1180","Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hawarden, Flint, Wales":"Hawarden, Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1160–":"environ 1160–Décédée","1165–1210":"1165–1210","1178–1231":"1178–1231","1180–Male":"1180–Dé